The Bushiris' supporters aren't giving up. Once again, they gathered at the Pretoria magistrate's court today. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala spoke to some of the protesters outside court. Courtesy #DStv403  PRETORIA - The Bushiris' supporters aren't giving up. Once again, they gathered at the Pretoria magistrate's court on Monday as police kept a watchful eye.
Self-proclaimed prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife Mary are still trying to convince the court why they should get bail. READ: Bushiri court case: Bail decision postponed It's been reported they make up one of the richest religious families in Africa. But Bushiri's congregants are firm that they want him freed.
They'll have to wait a bit longer though. Judgment in the bail application will only be handed down on Wednesday. Controversial religious leader Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, Mary, are spending at least another couple of nights behind bars. The ruling on their bail application was postponed to Wednesday. The Bushiris and three others are facing charges of fraud, theft and money laundering. Tshegohaco Moagi was in court. Courtesy #DStv403